[1] UK (Sussesx)
Date: Thu 26 Jul 2012
Source: ITV Meridian News [edited]
http://www.itv.com/news/meridian/update/2012-07-26/surge-in-measles-cases-in-sussex/

Surge in Measles cases in Sussex
----------------------------
There are more and more children suffering from measles in Sussex. So far this year, there have been 180 confirmed cases amongst children and adults in Brighton alone. Compare that with 86 in the rest of East Sussex, 38 in West Sussex, 21 in Kent , and in Essex just 6.

There has been 1 case in Oxfordshire, 5 in Berkshire and 9 in Surrey. There have been none in Buckinghamshire, Hampshire or the Isle of Wight.

The statistics are being blamed on the poor take-up of the MMR vaccine

